[{"id":"VH979137","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a horizontal beam of length L sub 0. The right end of the beam is attached to a hinge at point P on a vertical wall, and the left end of the beam is attached to a cable that is attached to the wall at a point above point P. The angle between the beam and the cable is labeled theta sub 0.\" height=\"206\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979137.g02.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A uniform horizontal beam of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L sub 0\"><math alttext=\"L sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is attached to a hinge at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, with the opposite end supported by a cable, as shown in the figure. The angle between the beam and the cable is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the magnitude of the torque that the cable exerts on the beam?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979137_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction M g L sub 0 over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction M g L sub 0 over 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><msub><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</m